text: 1st Tukatovo (; , 1-se Tükät) is a village in Nukayevsky Selsoviet, Kugarchinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 147 as of 2010. There are 2 streets. == Geography == It is located 30 km from Mrakovo, 5 km from Nukayevo. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kugarchinsky District
